        <title>The Terror</title>
        <author>Dan Simmons</author>
        <language>en</language>
        <link>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Terror_(novel)</link>
        <rating/>
        <publication-year>2007</publication-year>
        <review>&lt;b style="font-weight: bold; "&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 20px; font-family: sans-serif; font-weight: normal; "/&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; "&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&lt;i&gt;The Terror&lt;/i&gt;&#160;is the name of a 2007 novel by American author&#160;&lt;span class="yui-non"&gt;Dan Simmons&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 10px; "&gt;&#160;T&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;he novel is a fictionalized account of&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Franklin%27s_lost_expedition" title="Franklin's lost expedition" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;Captain Sir John Franklin's lost expedition&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&#160;of&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Erebus_(1826)" title="HMS Erebus (1826)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;HMS&#160;&lt;i&gt;Erebus&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&#160;and&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Terror_(1813)" title="HMS Terror (1813)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;HMS&lt;i&gt;Terror&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&#160;to the&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arctic" title="Arctic" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;Arctic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&#160;to force the&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwest_Passage" title="Northwest Passage" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;Northwest Passage&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&#160;in 1845 - 1848. In the novel, while Franklin and his crew are plagued by starvation and scurvy and forced to contend with mutiny and cannibalism, they are stalked across the bleak Arctic landscape by a monster.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;The characters featured in&#160;&lt;i&gt;The Terror&lt;/i&gt;&#160;are almost all actual members of Franklin's crew, whose unexplained disappearance has warranted a great deal of speculation. The main characters in the novel include Sir John Franklin, commander of the expedition and captain of&#160;&lt;i&gt;Erebus&lt;/i&gt;, Captain&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francis_Crozier" title="Francis Crozier" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Francis Crozier&lt;/a&gt;, captain of&#160;&lt;i&gt;Terror&lt;/i&gt;, Dr&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="new" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Harry_D.S_Goodsir&amp;amp;action=edit&amp;amp;redlink=1" title="Harry D.S Goodsir (page does not exist)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(204, 34, 0); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Harry D.S Goodsir&lt;/a&gt;, and Captain&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="new" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=James_Fitzjames&amp;amp;action=edit&amp;amp;redlink=1" title="James Fitzjames (page does not exist)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(204, 34, 0); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;James Fitzjames&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;In the final chapters of the book, Simmons explores and uses various aspects of&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eskimo" title="Eskimo" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Eskimo&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mythology" title="Mythology" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;mythology&lt;/a&gt;&#160;to explain the existence of the monster (called the&#160;&lt;i&gt;Tuunbaq&lt;/i&gt;) as a mythological creature made flesh, as well as its reasons for stalking and preying on the men of the Franklin Expedition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&lt;i&gt;The Terror&lt;/i&gt;&#160;was nominated for the British Fantasy Award in 2008.&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 11px; line-height: 15px; font-family: sans-serif; "&gt;Text is available under the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" rel="license" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Text_of_Creative_Commons_Attribution-ShareAlike_3.0_Unported_License" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike License&lt;/a&gt;; additional terms may apply. See&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" href="http://wikimediafoundation.org/wiki/Terms_of_Use" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Terms of Use&lt;/a&gt;&#160;for details.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;b/&gt;</review>
